REJMERGE(8)

# NAME

rejmerge - interactively resolve filesystem-staged package objects

# SYNOPSIS

*rejmerge* [*-hnv*] [*-r* _root-directory_]

# DESCRIPTION

*rejmerge* is the optional terminal frontend shipped with
*libpkgreconcile*(3).

It scans _/var/lib/pkg/rejected_, displays installed and staged differences,
and requests an explicit disposition for each candidate.

For paired objects, the frontend can keep installed contents, install staged
contents, create a two-way conflict copy for editing, select metadata, or skip
the candidate.

For relics without an installed counterpart, it can restore, relocate, delete,
or skip the staged object.

# OPTIONS

*-r* _root-directory_, *--root*=_root-directory_
	Operate on an alternate target root. The installed tree and staging tree
	are both interpreted below this root.

*-n*, *--dry-run*
	Inspect and display candidates without modifying either tree.

*-v*, *--version*
	Print the version and exit.

*-h*, *--help*
	Print usage and exit.

# ENVIRONMENT

*VISUAL*
	Editor command. Used before *EDITOR* when set.

*EDITOR*
	Editor command used when *VISUAL* is unset. The fallback is _/bin/vi_.

*PAGER*
	Pager command used for differences. The fallback is _/bin/more_.

*TMPDIR*
	Directory used for temporary conflict copies. The fallback is _/tmp_.

# FILES

_/var/lib/pkg/rejected/_
	Default mirrored staging tree.

# EXIT STATUS

*0*
	All requested work completed.

*1*
	Command-line misuse, insufficient privileges, closed input, stale state,
	or another operation failed.

# CAVEATS

Mutating operation requires superuser privileges. Dry-run may be executed by an
unprivileged user when file permissions permit inspection.

Conflict copies are literal two-way blocks. No common package ancestor is
available to the frontend, so this is not a three-way merge.

The command has no configuration-file interpreter.

# SEE ALSO

*libpkgreconcile*(3), *liblinediff*(3), *pkgadd*(8), *pkgman*(1)

